Actors, Dakore Egbuson, Ramsey Nouah, and Funke Akindele Bello were among the movie industry personalities that attended the Africa Movie Viewers’ Choice Awards (AMVCA) Sponsors Cocktail at Harbour Point, Victoria Island, Lagos. Amstel Malta, headline sponsor for this year’s AMVCA also had in attendance its brand representatives. The event was hosted by Ik Osakioduwa while Femi Leye entertained the audience with great music. The awards nominees were also in attendance to receive their certificates of nomination. According to Aminah Jagun, Senior Brand Manager Nigerian Breweries Plc: “For many years, Amstel Malta has celebrated Nollywood industry and our partnership with AMVCA further reinforces that. This year, we are committed to giving movie fans and enthusiasts access to front row seats at the industry’s biggest night while inspiring them to be their best.” With 104 nominees selected across 28 categories, Amstel Malta is proudly sponsoring 5 categories, namely Best Actor in a Drama (Movie/TV Series), Best Actress in a Drama (Movie/TV Series), Best Indigenous Language Movie/TV Series Igbo, Best Dressed of the Night,and Best Overall Movie. Africa Magic Viewers’ Choice Awards (AMVCA) holds on 14 March, 2020 at Eko Convention Center, Victoria Island, Lagos. See photos below: 